Program: Omnibus
Title: Odessa - Past and Present
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376ls8
Last Broadcast Date: 11 November 1998
A visit to Odessa which was built on the orders of Catherine the Great in 1794. The programme explores the city's unusual past and it's role in the newly independent Ukraine. Contributors include conductor Hobart Earle.